The paper discusses reinforcement learning for coordinating heterogeneous robotic platforms, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of Monte Carlo methods and policy space pruning techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of probably approximately local optimal (PALO) bounds for sample complexity analysis suggests a focus on mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
